South African Rail Agency Needs $744 Million Injection, Business Day Says

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-04-13T05:21:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/south-african-rail-agency-needs-744-million-injection-business-day-says.html
The Passenger Rail Agency of  South
Africa  needs a 5 billion rand cash injection from the government
to start its fleet modernization program, Business Day reported,
citing Chief Executive Officer Lucky  Montana .  Prasa, as the agency is known, needs to buy 2,000
locomotives and 8,600 coaches as it spends 97 billion rand over
the next 18 years renewing its fleet, the Johannesburg-based
newspaper said, citing Dries van der Walt, executive manager for
strategic development.  The agency also plans to partner with property companies to
redevelop 25 of its train stations, Business Day said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  